text: The Winnipeg Jets are an ice hockey team that plays in the NHL. The team plays in Winnipeg, Manitoba, Canada at Canada Life Centre. They were founded in 2011 when the Atlanta Thrashers were bought by Winnipeg-based company, True North Sports and Entertainment and were moved back to Winnipeg. The team announced the Winnipeg Jets as their name when they selected 7th in the first round of the 2011 NHL Entry Draft on June 25, 2011. Kevin Cheveldayoff was named its first General Manager on June 8, 2011 and Claude Noel was named the new head coach of the Jets on June 23, 2011.https://news.yahoo.com/s/ap/20110624/ap_on_sp_ho_ne/hkn_winnipeg_coach The original Winnipeg Jets played in the NHL from 1972 to 1996. This team is now known as the Arizona Coyotes. == References == ==Other websites== *Official website Category:2011 establishments in Canada
